Readme.md
   968Ôćĺ### .parse() and .parseAsync()
   970ÔćĺCall with no parameters to parse `process.argv`. Detects Electron and special node options like `node --eval`. Easy mode!
   971Ôćĺ
   972ÔćĺOr, call with an array of strings to parse, and optionally where the user arguments start by specifying where the arguments are `from`:
   973Ôćĺ
   974Ôćĺ- `'node'`: default, `argv[0]` is the application and `argv[1]` is the script being run, with user arguments after that
   975Ôćĺ- `'electron'`: `argv[0]` is the application and `argv[1]` varies depending on whether the electron application is packaged
   976Ôćĺ- `'user'`: just user arguments
   977Ôćĺ
   978ÔćĺFor example:
   979Ôćĺ
   980Ôćĺ```js
